### Bug Description:

| | Expected Behavior | Actual Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| After selecting item at index N | Focus stays at index N (or N-1 if N is last) | Focus **resets to index 0** |
| Down arrow after selection | Moves focus from index N to N+1 | Moves focus from index 0 to **index 1** |
| Net effect | User can continue browsing from current position | User is **jumped back to the top of the list** |

### Impact:
- **Severity: Medium-High** — Users using keyboard navigation for multiple selection are forced to re-navigate from the top of the list every time they make a selection, making multi-selection via keyboard extremely inefficient and counterintuitive.

### Root Cause (likely):
In the Dropdown component's `handleItemClick` or `selectItemByIndex` handler, when an item is selected in multiple mode, the `selectedIndex` state variable is being reset to `0` (or not properly maintained) instead of staying at the current position or being adjusted to the index of the next available item.
